<DOC><DOCNO> AP891010-0072 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-10-89 1129EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p PM-BRF--PaGovernor     10-10 0129</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Pa Governor,0134</SECOND><HEAD>Former Representative Announces Bid for Governor</HEAD><DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Former state Rep. John Kennedy today becamethe first announced candidate for the Republican nomination forgovernor.   Kennedy, 51, of Shiremanstown in central Pennsylvania, said heopposes abortion, an issue expected to be important in the Mayprimary, especially if he faces Auditor General Barbara Hafer.   Hafer is pro-choice and the leading but unannounced GOPcontender.   Gov. Robert P. Casey, a Democrat, is expected to seek a secondfour-year term in 1990.   Kennedy owns a business that builds and repairs railroad sidingsand last year unsuccessfully sought the GOP nomination for statetreasurer.   He served from 1980 to 1988 in the House and was considered amaverick for opposing higher pay and higher pensions forlegislators.</TEXT></DOC>